item.title: Orphaned case
item.dc:creator: @x_blitz_x x blitz x
item.description:
@x_blitz_x wrote:

[quote=“http://www.cs.brown.edu/courses/cs015/ota/compile_errors.shtml”]orphaned case.

The keyword “case” only has semantic meaning inside a switch statement. You may have accidently closed your switch statement with a misplaced “}”. Delete and retype all of your “}” characters and watch Emacs correspond "}"s with "{"s.[/quote]

Read full topic
